Reasoning: The paper proposes a method for learning Gaussian graphical models with a Gaussian prior on the parameters, which is tailored to high-dimensional problems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also proposes an efficient algorithm that performs a singular value decomposition of the training data, which suggests that it may also belong to the data structures (cs.DS) or information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. Finally, the paper shows promising results in several gene expression datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the bioinformatics (cs.SI) sub-category.
